PrecisAmendments to the CANADA GRAIN REGULATIONS which eliminate all maximum elevator tariffs, reduce (from one year to 90 days) the time period during which producers are entitled to make claims on securities held by the Commission, limit taxpayer liability in cases of default by licensed dealers and elevator operators, as well as revise the transportation rules to facilitate the movement of grain interprovincially and to export.
